System    log     or log system?
By   a    process a      socket               is      created.
By   any  process to the socket a message can be      sent.
Somewhere somehow    the          message     is      transcribed.
By        ascript a      socket   based
system    log     daemon                      is      provided.
System    log     via    UDP      and     TCP are not supported.

System    logs    sent    when  a
system    log     daemon  does    not exist   are     lost.
